headline: HP to cut up to 6,000 jobs: CEO talks AI push
summary: HP Inc. (HPQ) reported fiscal fourth quarter earnings results after the close on Tuesday, which topped Wall Street estimates on both the top and bottom lines. The company also announced it is pursuing new AI initiatives, which include reducing "gross global headcount by approximately 4,000-6,000 employees." HP CEO Enrique Lores sits down with Yahoo Finance Executive Editor Brian Sozzi to discuss the moves. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
